Class AbstractCommand

    • com.hula.lang.commands.AbstractCommand
  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:

    public abstract class AbstractCommand
extends java.lang.Object
implements Command
    This is an abstract implementation of the Command instance intended for extension by concrete Command implementations.

      • getVariableValue

        public java.lang.Object getVariableValue(java.lang.String parameterKey,
                                RuntimeConnector connector)
        Helper method which looks up the parameter value from the command signature. When the parameter value is a reference (prepended with $), it will lookup the variable value from the runtime variables.

        For example:

        CommandName name="MusicProduct" // returns a string object with value "MusicProduct"
        CommandName name=$typeName // returns the object referenced as 'typeName' in the runtime variables

      • assignVariable

        public void assignVariable(java.lang.String name,
                  java.lang.Object value,
                  RuntimeConnector connector)
        Helper method which sets a variable. If the value is a reference (prepended with $) it will lookup the referenced variable.

        For example:

        name="John" sets a variable with name=John
        name=$realname sets name to the value of variable $realname
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the variable to set
        value - The value of the variable to set
        connector - The RuntimeConnector to use

      • getVariableValueAsString
